Trump says increasing tariffs on Canada by 10%
subhead: The announcement comes two days after Trump said he had terminated all trade talks with Canada over what he called a 'fake' ad campaign. The ad from Ontario used quotes from a 1987 radio address on trade by Reagan, where he warned about the effects high tariffs on imports could have on the US economy.

title: French government under pressure over wealth tax proposal
subhead: Prime Minister Sébastien Lecornu, who has promised not to use a parliamentary tool employed by previous governments to force through unpopular measures, is under pressure from both the left and the right.

title: Japan is still in love with bears, despite increasingly frequent and deadly attacks
subhead: The rise in bear attacks has caused concern in a country deeply attached to the animal. Climate change and the declining rural population have driven bears to venture more often into residential areas.

title: On social media, women share their abortion stories to break the silence
subhead: In the face of misinformation and guilt-inducing rhetoric online, some users have chosen to speak openly about their abortions on these platforms. While sometimes it is simply a desire to share their personal experiences, more often, it remains a consciously political act.
